other_tests.procedure_name: Exploratory laparotomy with drainage of ascites
other_tests.findings: Optimal cytoreductive surgery with less than 1 cm of peritoneal disease remaining; pathologic findings consistent with epithelial ovarian cancer of mixed endometrioid/clear cell histology; metastatic adenocarcinoma noted in the left paracolic gutter.
Had cancer, uterus and fallopian tubes free of disease.
Part of the surgical management for ovarian cancer.
Part of the surgical management for ovarian cancer.
Participated in a clinical trial of maintenance abagovomab vs placebo, which did not show a PFS or overall survival benefit over placebo.
CA125 normalized after first cycle of chemotherapy with a nadir of 110 U/mL; CA125 considered part of routine follow-up.
